<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-09-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-09-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="694" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d694">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.05/164: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-10T17:00:00-04:00">September 10, 1929—5
                                    p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>302. Your 777, August 31, 6 p.m., and 802, September 7, 6 p.m., third
                                paragraph.<note n="86" xml:id="d694fn86">Latter not
                            printed.</note></p>
                        <pb facs="0839" n="695" xml:id="pg_695"/>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>I feel that the Powers should manifest a disposition to discuss
                                this question promptly and not stand on technicalities of procedure.
                                I desire that you inform your colleagues and Wang that you are ready
                                to go or to send a representative to Nanking for this
                                purpose.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Reference to Department’s 277 August 20, 6 p.m., especially
                                introductory paragraph and paragraph 4. Your views are again
                                invited.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>